General Assembly Proposed Bill No. 5074
February Session, 2026 LCO No. 790
Referred to Committee on APPROPRIATIONS
Introduced by:
REP. CARPINO, 32nd Dist.
REP. WOOD K., 29th Dist.
AN ACT CONCERNING FUNDING FOR FARMLAND PRESERVATION.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 That additional funds be appropriated to the Department of Energy
2 and Environmental Protection, from the General Fund, for the fiscal year
3 ending June 30, 2027, for farmland preservation.
Statement of Purpose:
To increase funding for farmland preservation.
